## EPIC EXAMPLE (Healthcare Domain):

**Epic Title:** Epic: Streamlined Appointment Scheduling for Patients in Healthcare Portal

**Epic Summary:**
Enable patients to book, reschedule, and cancel appointments through a self-service portal, reducing administrative burden on staff and improving patient satisfaction. This Epic will deliver a fully integrated scheduling system that connects with existing EMR and calendar systems.

**Business Context:**
Currently, patients must call the clinic during business hours to schedule appointments, resulting in long wait times, missed calls, and scheduling errors. The clinic receives 200+ scheduling calls daily, consuming 15% of front desk staff time. Patient satisfaction scores for appointment scheduling are 3.2/5.

**Epic Objectives:**
- Reduce scheduling call volume by 60%
- Improve appointment booking time from 10 minutes to under 3 minutes
- Increase patient satisfaction scores from 3.2 to 4.5
- Decrease no-show rates by 25% through automated reminders
- Enable 24/7 appointment scheduling access

**Success Metrics:**
- Baseline: 200 scheduling calls/day | Target: 80 calls/day
- Baseline: 10-minute average booking time | Target: 3 minutes
- Baseline: 3.2/5 satisfaction | Target: 4.5/5
- Baseline: 15% no-show rate | Target: 11.25% or lower
- System availability: 99.5% uptime

**Assumptions & Constraints:**
- EMR API is available and documented
- Patients have email addresses on file for notifications
- Clinic hours remain consistent (no complex scheduling rules)
- 6-month timeline with 2 developers and 1 designer
- Must work on mobile and desktop browsers
- HIPAA compliance required

**Risks:**
- **High likelihood, High impact**: EMR integration complexity may cause delays
  * Mitigation: Conduct technical spike in Sprint 1
- **Medium likelihood, High impact**: Low patient adoption due to technology barriers
  * Mitigation: Conduct usability testing with diverse age groups
- **Low likelihood, High impact**: Security vulnerabilities in authentication
  * Mitigation: Security review in design phase

**High-Level Scope:**

*In Scope:*
- Web and mobile browser appointment booking
- View available time slots by provider and specialty
- Reschedule and cancel existing appointments
- Automated email/SMS reminders
- Integration with EMR for provider schedules
- Patient authentication via existing portal login

*Out of Scope:*
- Phone-based scheduling automation
- Video visit scheduling (future epic)
- Provider-side schedule management (separate epic)
- Insurance verification during booking

**Epic-Level Acceptance Criteria:**
- Patients can successfully book appointments for any available provider slot
- Appointments booked through portal sync with EMR within 30 seconds
- Patients receive confirmation emails within 1 minute of booking
- System handles 100 concurrent users without performance degradation
- All HIPAA security requirements met and documented
- 90% of users complete booking without assistance

**Dependencies:**

*Upstream:*
- EMR API access granted by vendor (ETA: Sprint 1)
- Portal authentication system upgraded (In Progress - Team B)

*Downstream:*
- Automated reminders Epic (planned Q2)
- Provider mobile app notifications (planned Q3)

*External:*
